content:
Schedule a Report for Refresh

You can schedule a report to run daily, weekly, or monthly. An HTML version of the report can be sent by email to users in your organization.

To create a schedule, click Schedule Future Runs from the Run Report dropdown menu on the Reports tab. You'll need Enhanced Folder Sharing and permission to create, edit, and delete reports.

On the Schedule Report page, specify a running user who has access to the folder where the report is stored. The access level of the running user determines what other users see when they receive the scheduled report run results.

Select an email setting: To me, To me and/or others. You can send reports only to email addresses included on Salesforce user records.

Set the frequency, duration, and time for running the report:

* Frequency: Daily, Weekly, or Monthly
* Start and End dates: specify the dates during which you want to schedule the report
* Preferred Start Time: choose a start time

Click Save Report Schedule. You can choose to save report modifications with this schedule or discard them.

Report recipients can click the report name in emailed reports to log in to Salesforce and view the report directly.

You need Enhanced Folder Sharing, permission to create, edit, and delete reports, and the “View All Data” permission to specify a running user other than yourself. If the running user becomes inactive, the report doesn’t run, and Salesforce sends an email notification to either activate the user, delete the report schedule, or change the running user to an active one.

See also: Manage a Report’s Schedule
title: Scheduling Reports in Salesforce
